</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-65B4A85E-9951-470E-82B1-70FC7EB25877"><p class="- topic/p "> When analyzing print quality of a image, always view perpendicular and the image should be judged in a vertical position. When analyzing uniformity of solid areas of PQT chart for banding defects the recommended distance to view is: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PQT in Specialty matte or gloss (8 pass) print mode should be analyzed from Very close range (1 meter) (39.4"). 
</p></li></ul></note><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-D24C5DD5-5CAC-46B6-BD81-11E87BECD0C5"><p class="- topic/p "> When analyzing print quality like sharpness, graininess, viewing distance should be fine details range (50 cm) (19.7"). 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-EF42FFF3-C6AF-4939-AE5C-9EB2061E0E1B.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Image Quality</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
